INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('8553', '2', 'Ingredients1/2 cup uncooked quinoa, rinsed and drained1 cup water5 asparagus spears, shaved thin (use a vegetable peeler)1 handful fresh baby arugula, roughly chopped1 green onion, chopped2 Tablespoons lemon juice, fresh squeezed2Tablespoons extra virgin olive oil1/2ripe avocado, peeled, pitted and diced2 Tablespoons fresh dill, chopped (optional)Salt and freshly ground pepper'),
('8553', '3', 'In a medium saucepan combine quinoa and water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, about 12- 15 minutes or until liquid is completely absorbed. Meanwhile In a mixing bowl, make the dressing by whisking together lemon juice and oil.'),
('8553', '4', 'Add avocado, green onion and arugula to the dressing.'),
('8553', '5', 'Transfer quinoa to a medium bowl and allow to cool.'),
('8553', '6', 'Add quinoa to dressing and vegetable mixture; toss with fresh dill and season with salt and pepper to taste.'),
('8553', '7', 'Serve at room temperature.Enjoy!Here are just a few interesting quinoa recipes from fellow bloggers:Stuffed Cabbage with Quinoa & Roasted Sweet Potatoes from Karina''s Kitchen'),
('8553', '8', 'Quinoa Pudding with Macerated Strawberries & Pistachios from Cannelle & Vanille'),
('8553', '9', 'Quinoa Salad with Tomato, Feta and Parsley from The Perfect Pantry'),
('8553', '10', 'Quinoa with Roasted Radishes & Pearl Onions from FatFree Vegan Kitchen'),
('8553', '11', 'Warm & Nutty Cinnamon Quinoa from 101 Cookbooks'),
('8553', '12', 'Quinoa Pilaf from Simply Recipes'),
('8554', '1', 'Scrape the batter into the pan(s).'),
('8554', '2', 'Bake until the cake tester comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes. Cool the cake in the pan(s) on a rack for about 15 minutes before unmolding.You can make this cake 2-3 days ahead for the trifle; in fact its great if its a tiny bit stale.my roommate Caitlyns beautiful handiwork: a swan doggy bag for Alex'),
('8555', '1', 'In a small bowl, mix the lemon juice with the truffle oil and season with salt and pepper. Set aside until ready to use.'),
('8555', '2', 'Using a mandoline, slice the celery root very thinly. Stack the slices and cut them into very fine strips.'),
('8555', '3', 'In a large bowl, toss the arugula with the pea shoots, celery root and smoked salmon.'),
('8555', '4', 'Add the dressing and toss well. Mound the salad on plates and serve.'),
('8557', '1', 'Light a grill.'),
('8557', '2', 'Brush the ears of corn with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Lightly brush the grill with the vegetable oil and grill the corn over a medium-hot fire, turning frequently, until lightly charred and almost tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('8557', '3', 'Let cool slightly. Over a bowl, cut the kernels from the cobs.'),
('8557', '4', 'In a saucepan of boiling salted water, cook the black-eyed peas until tender, about 12 minutes.'),
('8557', '5', 'Drain and refresh under cold water.'),
('8557', '6', 'Drain and pat dry.'),
('8557', '7', 'In a large bowl, whisk the 1/3 cup of olive oil with the lime juice and balsamic vinegar. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('8557', '8', 'Add the grilled corn, black-eyed peas, red bell peppers, onion, cilantro and jalapeos and toss well. Season generously with salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or for up to 4 hours. Toss the black-eyed pea salad with the arugula and transfer to a platter just before serving.'),
('8561', '1', 'Toss the arugula with the lemons.'),
('8561', '2', 'Drizzle with extra-virgin olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss again. Scatter the Parmesan on top; serve at once. Or, to prevent the salad from wilting on the buffet table, set out a bottle of olive oil next to the ingredients in separate bowls and have your guests assemble their own salads.'),
('8563', '1', 'In a small bowl, stir together the pear nectar and vinegar. Season with salt and pepper. Set the dressing aside.'),
('8563', '2', 'Cut off the stems and feathery tops and any bruised outer stalks from the fennel bulb.'),
('8563', '3', 'Cut the fennel bulb in half lengthwise and cut away and discard the core. Slice crosswise paper-thin. Set aside.In a bowl, combine the mesclun and arugula.'),
('8563', '4', 'Add half of the dressing and toss well. Divide the greens evenly among individual plates. Top the greens with the fennel, prosciutto and figs and drizzle with the remaining dressing. Using a cheese plane or a vegetable peeler, shave thin slices from the cheese and sprinkle over the salads. Season with pepper and serve.'),
('8566', '1', 'Lets get started.Preheat oven to 350F. Slice the potatoes and place in a glass casserole dish with about 2 tbsp water in the bottom. Roast potatoes for about 10 minutes. Slice pear and set aside.'),
('8567', '1', 'Reduce heat to low or medium-low.'),
('8567', '2', 'Add olive oil to the pan. Crack three eggs into the pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover pan with a lid. After about 3 minutes, check eggs. Cook until theyre reached your desired doneness. I usually cook eggs for about 4 minutes.'),
('8567', '3', 'Remove skillet from heat. Sprinkle the eggs with bacon, mushrooms, and arugula.'),
('8567', '4', 'Add more salt and pepper as necessary and serve immediately.'),
('8567', '5', 'Serve with crusty bread and hot sauce.'),
('8569', '1', 'Place lentils and 1 onion half in a medium saucepan; cover with cold water by 2 inches. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer, partially covered, stirring occasionally, until lentils are tender, about 20 minutes.'),
('8569', '2', 'Drain; discard onion half.'),
('8569', '3', 'Transfer lentils to a medium bowl.'),
('8570', '1', 'Heat oven to 400 F.'),
('8570', '2', 'Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Season the lamb with 3/4 teaspoon of the salt and 3/4 teaspoon of the pepper.'),
('8570', '3', 'Add 4 of the chops to the skillet and cook until browned, about 2 minutes per side.'),
('8570', '4', 'Transfer to a baking sheet. Repeat with the remaining chops. Roast to the desired doneness, 4 to 6 minutes for medium-rare. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine the tomatoes, garlic, fennel, lemon juice, oregano, and the remaining oil, salt, and pepper. Divide the arugula and lamb chops among individual plates and spoon the tomato mixture over the greens. Tip: The bright, refreshing flavors of the tomato, fennel, and arugula salad also go well with seared steak or salmon.'),
('8572', '1', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray. Sprinkle beef with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.'),
('8572', '2', 'Add beef to pan; cook 4 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('8572', '3', 'Remove beef from pan; keep warm.'),
('8572', '4', 'Melt butter in pan; coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('8572', '5', 'Add remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, remaining 1/8 teaspoon pepper, red onion, and mushrooms to pan; saut 4 minutes or until mushrooms release their liquid.'),
('8572', '6', 'Combine juice and arugula in a large bowl.'),
('8572', '7', 'Add mushroom mixture to arugula mixture; toss gently to combine. Arrange 1 1/2 cups salad mixture on each of 4 plates; top each serving with 1 steak.'),
('8573', '1', 'Heat oven to 400 F. Thinly slice the tenderloin on a diagonal into 8 pieces. Pound the slices to a 1/4-inch thickness.'),
('8573', '2', 'Place the flour on a plate.'),
('8573', '3', 'Place the eggs in a shallow bowl and beat lightly. In a separate bowl, combine the bread crumbs, salt, and Parmesan. Working in batches, lightly coat the cutlets first in the flour, then in the egg mixture (allowing any excess to drip off), and finally in the bread crumb mixture.'),
('8573', '4', 'Heat 2 tablespoons of the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('8573', '5', 'Add 4 of the cutlets. Cook until golden, 1 to 2 minutes per side.'),
('8573', '6', 'Place the cutlets on a baking sheet. Wipe out the skillet and repeat with the remaining olive oil and cutlets.'),
('8573', '7', 'Transfer to oven and heat until the pork is cooked through, 8 to 10 minutes. Divide the arugula and tomatoes among individual plates and drizzle with the extra-virgin olive oil.'),
('8573', '8', 'Serve with the cutlets and lemon wedges.Tip: When it''s not peak tomato season, try using intensely flavored Roma (plum) tomatoes instead of tomatoes on the vine. Use 2 Romas for each regular tomato.'),
('8575', '1', 'Cook bacon in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat until crisp.'),
('8575', '2', 'Remove bacon from the pan, reserving 1 teaspoon drippings in pan. Crumble bacon, and set aside.'),
('8575', '3', 'Add shrimp to drippings in the pan; saut 5 minutes or until done. Using a slotted spoon, transfer shrimp to a large bowl.'),
('8575', '4', 'Add arugula leaves and halved cherry tomatoes to shrimp; toss gently.'),
('8575', '5', 'Combine yogurt, vinegar, oil, and pepper in a small bowl, stirring well with a whisk.'),
('8575', '6', 'Drizzle vinegar mixture over shrimp mixture; toss gently to combine.'),
('8575', '7', 'Place 2 1/4 cups salad mixture on each of 4 plates; divide crumbled bacon evenly among salads.'),
('8576', '1', 'Preheat oven to 45'),
('8576', '2', 'Unroll pizza dough on a baking sheet lightly coated with cooking spray; place in preheating oven.'),
('8576', '3', 'Bake as oven heats for 7 minutes.'),
('8576', '4', 'Combine the ricotta and 1/4 cup Romano.'),
('8576', '5', 'Remove pan from oven. Quickly spread cheese mixture over dough, leaving a 1/2-inch border around the edges. Return pan to oven, and bake for 5 minutes.'),
('8576', '6', 'While pizza bakes, add water to a large skillet, filling two-thirds full; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer.'),
('8576', '7', 'Add vinegar. Break each egg into a custard cup, and pour gently into pan. Cook 3 minutes or until desired degree of doneness. Carefully remove eggs from pan using a slotted spoon.'),
('8576', '8', 'Combine arugula, remaining 1/4 cup Romano cheese, and the next 4 ingredients (through salt) in a large bowl; toss well. Top pizza with arugula mixture and eggs; sprinkle with pepper.'),
('8576', '9', 'Cut into 6 pieces.'),
('8577', '1', 'In a medium bowl, toss together the arugula, beans, pesto, and  teaspoon each kosher salt and black pepper.'),
('8578', '1', 'Combine the onion, celery, carrot, prosciutto, parsley, garlic and cayenne pepper in a pot with about 8 cups of water. Season the water with salt and boil for 5 minutes to allow the flavors to infuse.'),
('8578', '2', 'Add the octopus and reduce the heat to medium-low. Simmer gently for about 1 hour or until the octopus is tender when gently pierced with a knife. Cool the octopus in the braising liquid at room temperature until cool enough to handle.'),
('8578', '3', 'Remove the octopus from the braising liquid and drain well.'),
('8578', '4', 'Heat a cast-iron skillet or a flat griddle over high heat until it is very hot. Season the octopus with olive oil, salt and pepper. Grill the octopus until it is caramelized and crusted on all sides, about 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('8578', '5', 'Transfer the charred octopus to a cutting board and cut each tentacle on the bias into 4 slices.'),
('8578', '6', 'Place the octopus slices in the center of 4 plates and garnish with arugula and 3 to 4 slices of the peach.'),
('8578', '7', 'Drizzle 1 tablespoon of aged balsamic vinegar over and around the octopus, and finish each dish with a squeeze of lemon juice.'),
('8578', '8', 'Serve immediately.'),
('8578', '9', 'Reprinted with permission from Avec Ripert: A Culinary Journey with Eric Ripert by Eric Ripert with Angie Mosier and Soa Davies, (C) 2010 John Wiley & Sons, Inc.'),
('8579', '1', 'Heat olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.'),
('8579', '2', 'Add the shallots, and cook for 4 minutes. Stir in the rice, and saut for 2 minutes.'),
('8579', '3', 'Add the broth, wine, salt, and pepper, and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 20 minutes. Stir in arugula and pistachios.'),
('8580', '1', 'Combine mayonnaise, dill, water, sherry vinegar, Dijon mustard, black pepper, and salt in a large bowl; stir with a whisk.'),
('8580', '2', 'Add frise, baby arugula, fennel bulb, cucumber, and radish. Toss gently to combine. Sprinkle with toasted pine nuts.'),
('8583', '1', 'Rinse the scallops and dry well with paper towels. Season the scallops with salt and pepper. In a large, heavy fry pan over high heat, warm the olive oil until it shimmers. In batches without crowding, add the scallops and sear until nicely browned on one side, about 2 minutes. Turn the scallops over and brown the other side, about 1 minute more. Return all the scallops to the pan, add the lemon zest and thyme, and cook for a moment. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the scallops to a bowl. Reduce the heat to low and add the butter and shallots to the pan. Saut until softened, about 4 minutes.Meanwhile, bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat. Generously salt the boiling water, add the pasta and cook until al dente (tender but firm to the bite), 3 to 4 minutes.While the pasta is cooking, add the lemon juice and stock to the fry pan and deglaze the pan, stirring to scrape up the browned bits from the bottom. Simmer until slightly thickened, 3 to 4 minutes.'),
('8583', '2', 'Drain the pasta well and add it to the fry pan.'),
('8583', '3', 'Add the scallops and any juices that have accumulated, then add the capers and pine nuts. Toss over low heat to finish cooking the scallops and mix the ingredients, about 1 minute. Taste and adjust the seasonings.'),
('8583', '4', 'Transfer to a warmed large, shallow bowl, add the arugula leaves and toss gently.'),
('8583', '5', 'Serve immediately.'),
('8583', '6', 'Serves 4.'),
('8586', '1', 'Scatter the arugula in a wide, shallow serving bowl.'),
('8586', '2', 'Heat a large (preferably 12- inch) skillet over medium-high heat for 1 minute.'),
('8586', '3', 'Pour in 2 Tbs. of the oil and swirl to coat the pan. As soon as the oil is shimmeringbut not smokingadd the fennel and onion in an even layer. Season with salt and pepper and let the vegetables cook undisturbed until they have begun to brown, about 2 minutes. Stir occasionally until the fennel and onion are tender and deep golden brown in places, about another 5 minutes. If the vegetables seem to be cooking too fast or the bottom of the pan is starting to burn, lower the heat to medium. (If using an electric stovetop, take the pan off the burner momentarily to let the pan cool.) Clear a space in the center of the pan and add the remaining 1/2 Tbs. oil and then the garlic.'),
('8586', '4', 'Let cook until the garlic is fragrant, about 30 seconds.'),
('8586', '5', 'Add the orange juice and stir to combine with the vegetables.'),
('8586', '6', 'Pour the mixture over the arugula and toss to combine and to wilt the arugula. Season to taste with salt and pepper, sprinkle with the chopped olives and and serve immediately.    Serving Suggestions'),
('8590', '1', 'Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan. Stir in uncooked couscous and salt.'),
('8590', '2', 'Remove from heat; cover and let stand 10 minutes. Fluff couscous with a fork. Stir in arugula, olive oil, lemon juice, and black pepper.'),
('8591', '1', 'Spread 1 side of 6 bread slices with blue cheese. Layer with turkey, cranberry sauce, pancetta, and arugula.'),
('8591', '2', 'Spread 1 side of remaining 6 bread slices with mustard, and place, mustard sides down, on arugula.'),
('8591', '3', 'Note: We tested with Saga Classic Soft-Ripened Blue-Veined Cheese.'),
('8591', '4', 'Bacon-Horseradish-Turkey Sandwiches: Substitute 6 split croissants for bread, 6 Havarti cheese slices for blue cheese, 6 cooked bacon slices for pancetta, and peach preserves for cranberry sauce. Stir 1 Tbsp. refrigerated horseradish into peach preserves. Proceed as directed.'),
('8593', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring with a whisk.'),
('8593', '2', 'Peel oranges, and cut each crosswise into 6 slices. Arrange 6 orange slices on each of 6 arugula-lined plates. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon feta over each salad, and drizzle each with 1 tablespoon dressing.'),
('8595', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375 degrees.'),
('8595', '2', 'Place walnuts on a rimmed baking sheet. Toast in oven until fragrant, about 8 minutes.'),
('8595', '3', 'Let cool slightly. Finely chop, and set aside.'),
('8598', '1', 'Bring broth to a boil in a small pot.'),
('8598', '2', 'Heat oil and garlic in a medium saucepan over medium heat until garlic just begins to turn golden (don''t let it get dark or the oil will taste bitter). Carefully lift out the garlic halves and discard.'),
('8598', '3', 'Add couscous to hot oil and fry until it begins to get golden and toasty all over, stirring constantly, ~3-5 minutes. If couscous doesn''t seem to be getting colored right away, raise the heat a bit. CAREFULLY pour in the hot broth (stand back, it may spit & spatter) and give everything a stir. Put a tight lid on the pan. Turn off the heat and let sit for 10 minutes. Using a fork, fluff the couscous. Turn it out into a large serving bowl and add the zest and juice of the lemon, the sliced scallions, and the baby arugula. Toss gently. Season to taste with salt and pepper, then toss again. Enjoy as an accompaniment to a meal...or if you''re like me, eat it AS the meal.'),
('8600', '1', 'In a large nonstick skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the olive oil.'),
('8600', '2', 'Add the mushrooms and season with salt and pepper. Cook over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until tender and lightly browned, about 6 minutes.'),
('8600', '3', 'Transfer the mushrooms to a bowl and let cool.'),
('8600', '4', 'In a large bowl, whisk the vinegar with the lemon zest and the remaining 1/4 cup of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('8600', '5', 'Add the celery matchsticks, arugula and mushrooms and gently toss.'),
('8600', '6', 'Transfer the salad to a large platter or bowl, top with the Pecorino Toscano, prosciutto and celery leaves and serve right away.'),
('8602', '1', 'Preheat oven to 45'),
('8602', '2', 'Place dough in a bowl coated with cooking spray; let dough stand, covered, for 15 minutes.'),
('8602', '3', 'Cook bacon in a skillet over medium heat until crisp.'),
('8602', '4', 'Remove bacon; crumble.'),
('8602', '5', 'Add tomatoes and pepper to drippings in pan; cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('8602', '6', 'Sprinkle a baking sheet with cornmeal; roll dough into a 12-inch circle on prepared baking sheet.'),
('8602', '7', 'Spread sauce evenly over dough, leaving a 1/2-inch border. Top with tomatoes and bacon. Sprinkle cheese over top.'),
('8602', '8', 'Bake at 450 on bottom oven rack for 17 minutes or until crust is golden.'),
('8602', '9', 'Combine arugula and remaining ingredients; top pizza with arugula mixture.'),
('8603', '1', 'In a small bowl, whisk all dressing ingredients except oil.'),
('8603', '2', 'Whisk in oil. In a bowl, toss arugula, pomegranate seeds and pears with dressing; serve.'),
('8604', '1', 'Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.'),
('8604', '2', 'Drain in a colander over a bowl, reserving 2/3 cup cooking liquid.'),
('8604', '3', 'While pasta cooks, heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('8604', '4', 'Remove casings from sausage. Break sausage into bite-sized pieces and add to pan; cook 3 minutes or until browned, stirring frequently to crumble.'),
('8604', '5', 'Add garlic; cook 30 seconds, stirring constantly.'),
('8604', '6', 'Add tomatoes and pepper; cover and cook 2 minutes. Mash tomatoes with the back of a wooden spoon to break them up. Cover pan; reduce heat to low, and cook 3 minutes.'),
('8604', '7', 'Remove pan from heat.'),
('8604', '8', 'Add pasta, reserved 2/3 cup cooking liquid, and arugula; toss well. Sprinkle with pecorino Romano.'),
('8606', '1', 'Cook barley according to package directions, omitting salt.'),
('8606', '2', 'Combine barley, arugula, bell pepper, tomatoes, and chickpeas in a large bowl.'),
('8606', '3', 'Combine lemon juice, oil, salt, and crushed red pepper, stirring with a whisk.'),
('8606', '4', 'Drizzle over barley mixture, and toss. Sprinkle with pistachios.'),
('8607', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('8607', '2', 'Heat a grill pan coated with cooking spray over medium-high heat.'),
('8607', '3', 'Place each chicken breast half between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap, and pound each piece to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Sprinkle both sides evenly with 1/8 teaspoon salt and black pepper.'),
('8607', '4', 'Add chicken to pan, and cook 4 minutes on each side or until done.'),
('8607', '5', 'While chicken cooks, combine 1/8 teaspoon salt, tomatoes, vinegar, and garlic, stirring with a whisk.'),
('8607', '6', 'Place buns, cut sides up, on a baking sheet. Broil 1 minute or until lightly toasted.'),
('8607', '7', 'Place 1 chicken breast half on bottom half of each bun.'),
('8607', '8', 'Add arugula to tomato mixture, and toss gently to coat. Arrange about 1/2 cup arugula mixture over each chicken breast half. Cover with tops of buns.'),
('8608', '1', 'Preheat oven to 42'),
('8608', '2', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring with a whisk.'),
('8608', '3', 'Add figs; toss to coat.'),
('8608', '4', 'Remove figs with a slotted spoon, reserving vinegar mixture.'),
('8608', '5', 'Place figs in a cast-iron or ovenproof skillet coated with cooking spray.'),
('8608', '6', 'Bake at 425 for 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('8608', '7', 'Remove figs from pan; place on a plate. Immediately add reserved vinegar mixture to hot pan, scraping pan to loosen browned bits.'),
('8608', '8', 'Pour into a small bowl; let figs and vinaigrette cool to room temperature.'),
('8608', '9', 'Place arugula on a platter; arrange figs over arugula. Sprinkle with cheese and pepper.'),
('8608', '10', 'Drizzle with cooled vinaigrette.'),
('8609', '1', 'Place first 6 ingredients in a food processor; pulse 7 or 8 times or until mixture forms a smooth paste.'),
('8609', '2', 'Add cheese, broth, salt, and pepper; pulse until combined.'),
('8609', '3', 'Combine pesto and pasta in a large bowl, tossing to coat.'),
('8610', '1', 'Combine lemon rind, juice, oil, and garlic in a large bowl. Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('8610', '2', 'Add arugula; toss well.'),
('8610', '3', 'Place each chicken breast half between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; pound each piece to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or small heavy skillet. Sprinkle both sides of chicken with remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt and remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('8610', '4', 'Heat a grill pan or a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('8610', '5', 'Add chicken, and cook for 4 minutes on each side or until done.'),
('8610', '6', 'Remove chicken from pan, and keep warm.'),
('8610', '7', 'Add halved tomatoes and dry white wine to pan. Cook for 2 minutes or until the liquid almost evaporates.'),
('8611', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well with a whisk.'),
('8611', '2', 'Add figs; cover and let stand 20 minutes.'),
('8611', '3', 'Add arugula and pepper; toss well. Top with cheese.'),
('8611', '4', 'Serve immediately.'),
('8612', '1', 'Combine yogurt and 1 tablespoon Rosemary-Garlic Rub.'),
('8612', '2', 'Remove the Mediterranean Grilled Chicken from bones; thinly slice.'),
('8612', '3', 'Combine juice, oil, salt, and pepper; drizzle over arugula, tossing to coat.'),
('8612', '4', 'Spread yogurt mixture over cut sides of bread. Arrange arugula, sliced chicken, onion, and olives over bottom half of loaf; cover with top half of loaf.'),
('8612', '5', 'Cut into 4 wedges.'),
('8612', '6', '(Totals include Rosemary-Garlic Rub and Mediterranean Grilled Chicken)'),
('8613', '1', 'Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.'),
('8613', '2', 'Heat a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('8613', '3', 'Add 2 tablespoons oil to pan; swirl to coat.'),
('8613', '4', 'Add rosemary, pepper, and garlic to pan; cook 2 minutes or until garlic is tender, stirring constantly. Increase heat to medium-high.'),
('8613', '5', 'Add shrimp to pan; saut for 6 minutes or until shrimp are done.'),
('8613', '6', 'Remove shrimp mixture from pan.'),
('8613', '7', 'Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil and vinegar to pan; cook for 15 seconds.'),
('8613', '8', 'Drizzle warm vinegar mixture over arugula mixture; toss gently to coat. Divide arugula mixture among 4 plates; top with shrimp.'),
('8613', '9', 'Serve immediately.'),
('8614', '1', 'In a small bowl, whisk the olive oil with the lemon juice, honey and chopped thyme. Season the salad dressing with salt and pepper.'),
('8614', '2', 'In a large bowl, toss the arugula with the pear slices and pumpkin seeds.'),
('8614', '3', 'Add the dressing and toss well. Top with the crumbled goat cheese, sprinkle lightly with sea salt and serve right away.'),
('8615', '1', 'Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.'),
('8615', '2', 'Add pasta and arugula, and toss gently.'),
('8615', '3', 'Place 2 cups pasta mixture in each of 4 bowls, and sprinkle with cheese.'),
('8617', '1', 'Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well with a whisk.'),
('8617', '2', 'Add lettuce, onion, Parmesan, and walnuts; toss gently to coat.'),
('8618', '1', 'Prepare grill to medium-high heat.'),
('8618', '2', 'Place chicken between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; pound each piece to 1/2-inch thickness using a meat mallet or small heavy skillet. Sprinkle chicken with parsley, tarragon, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('8618', '3', 'Place chicken on grill rack coated with cooking spray; grill 4 minutes on each side or until done.'),
('8618', '4', 'Transfer to a plate; cool to room temperature.'),
('8618', '5', 'Combine oil, vinegar, remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, and dash of pepper in a small bowl, stirring with a whisk.'),
('8618', '6', 'Combine arugula, greens, apricots, and onion in a large bowl.'),
('8618', '7', 'Pour vinaigrette over arugula mixture; toss well to coat.'),
('8618', '8', 'Place about 2 cups arugula mixture on each of 4 plates.'),
('8618', '9', 'Cut chicken breast halves crosswise into thin slices; top each serving evenly with chicken.'),
('8618', '10', 'Serve immediately.'),
('8618', '11', 'Wine note: In this salad, arugula''s peppery bite is nicely balanced by fragrant herbs, sweet apricots, and grilled chicken. A great wine with a complexly flavored salad like this is pinot gris from Oregon. It has a fresh, clean feel and a creamy, fruity flavor. Two favorites: Lemelson Tikka''s Run and Chehalem, both 2007 from the Willamette Valley, and both $ Karen MacNeil'),
('8619', '1', 'Combine vinegar, honey, syrup, and mustard in a small bowl. Gradually add oil, stirring with a whisk.'),
('8619', '2', 'Combine arugula, grapes, seeds, and thyme in a large bowl.'),
('8619', '3', 'Drizzle vinegar mixture over arugula; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Toss gently to coat.'),
('8620', '1', 'Position oven rack to lowest setting. Preheat oven to 500'),
('8620', '2', 'Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray; sprinkle with cornmeal. Unroll dough onto prepared baking sheet, and pat into a 14 x 10-inch rectangle.'),
('8620', '3', 'Spread the pesto evenly over dough, leaving a 1/2-inch border. Sprinkle mozzarella cheese over pesto.'),
('8620', '4', 'Place baking sheet on the bottom oven rack; bake at 500 for 5 minutes.'),
('8620', '5', 'Remove pizza from oven.'),
('8620', '6', 'Coarsely chop artichokes. Arrange artichokes on pizza; top with sliced prosciutto. Sprinkle with Parmesan. Return pizza to the bottom oven rack; bake an additional 6 minutes or until crust is browned.'),
('8620', '7', 'Place arugula in a bowl.'),
('8620', '8', 'Drizzle juice over arugula; toss gently. Top the pizza with arugula mixture.'),
('8620', '9', 'Cut the pizza into 4 (7 x 5-inch) rectangles; cut each rectangle diagonally into 2 wedges.'),
('8621', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('8621', '2', 'Place the arugula and watermelon in a large bowl. In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper.'),
('8621', '3', 'Pour enough dressing on the arugula to moisten. Toss well and place on 6 salad plates.'),
('8621', '4', 'With a very sharp knife or a vegetable peeler, shave the Parmesan into large shards and sprinkle them on the arugula and watermelon. Sprinkle with salt and serve.'),
('8622', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350 F. In a small bowl, combine the arugula, olive oil, and garlic. Separate the arugula mixture between 4 ramekins. Crack an egg in the center of each ramekin. Top the ramekins with the Parmesan cheese and chives. Lightly sprinkle with a bit of kosher salt.'),
('8622', '2', 'Place the ramekins on a baking sheet.'),
('8622', '3', 'Bake for 10-14 minutes or until the egg is nearly set. It should still be slightly soft.'),
('8622', '4', 'Remove from the oven and allow it to rest for 3-5 minutes for the egg to completely set.'),
('8622', '5', 'Serve warm.Makes 4 baked eggs.'),
('8623', '1', 'Combine all ingredients in a food processor and run until combined.'),
('8623', '2', 'Add more lemon juice or olive oil if the consistency is too thick ( I cheated and added a little water to thin mine down.)Enjoy on sandwiches, eggs, and pasta.*I used almonds because pine nuts were $32.99 a pound at my local store- another option would be toasted walnuts.'),
('8624', '1', 'Combine olive oil, lemon rind, lemon juice, and salt in a large bowl.'),
('8624', '2', 'Add arugula and onion; toss well.'),
('8625', '1', 'To make sauce, combine tomatoes, basil, garlic, and 1 tbsp oil in a medium-sized bowl. Stir well and set aside for up to 1 hour.'),
('8625', '2', 'Mix cheeses together in a bowl. In a separate bowl, combine arugula, remaining 2 tbsp oil, and vinegar. Season with salt and pepper. Make crust. While second side of each crust is grilling, spread 1/8 cheese mixture over cooked side of each crust; dollop each with1/3 cup sauce. (Do not spread.) Top with arugula. Rotate 3 to 4 minutes until bottom is golden brown.To make sauce, combine tomatoes, basil, garlic, and 1 tbsp oil in a medium-sized bowl. Stir well and set aside for up to 1 hour.'),
('8625', '3', 'Mix cheeses together in a bowl. In a separate bowl, combine arugula, remaining 2 tbsp oil, and vinegar. Season with salt and pepper. Make crust. While second side of each crust is grilling, spread 1/8 cheese mixture over cooked side of each crust; dollop each with1/3 cup sauce. (Do not spread.) Top with arugula. Rotate 3 to 4 minutes until bottom is golden brown.'),
('8626', '1', 'Whisk lemon juice, olive oil, salt and pepper.Lay the roast beef over a plate.'),
('8626', '2', 'Add half of the vinaigrette to the roast beef. Top with arugula, salt, pepper, remaining vinaigrette and shaved Asiago.'),
('8626', '3', 'Serve immediately.Print This2 PP 2 SP Appetizers Lunch Recipes Springposted April 27, 2010 by Gina7 Comments'),
('8627', '1', 'Light a grill. In a small skillet, toast the mustard and cumin seeds over moderately high heat until fragrant, about 1 minute.'),
('8627', '2', 'Let cool, then transfer the seeds to a mortar or spice grinder and grind to a powder. Rub the spices all over the lamb and season with salt and pepper.'),
('8627', '3', 'Grill the lamb over moderately high heat, turning and rotating the racks occasionally, until lightly charred outside and medium-rare within, about 30 minutes total.'),
('8627', '4', 'Transfer the lamb to a carving board and let rest for 10 minutes.'),
('8627', '5', 'Meanwhile, in a food processor, puree the arugula with the garlic, lemon juice and olive oil.'),
('8627', '6', 'Add the cheese and season the pesto with salt and pepper.'),
('8627', '7', 'Carve the lamb racks into individual chops and transfer to plates.'),
('8627', '8', 'Serve the arugula pesto alongside.'),
('8629', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('8629', '2', 'Line a baking sheet with foil. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F.'),
('8629', '3', 'Whisk the vinegar, shallots, and honey in a medium bowl to blend. Gradually whisk in the oil. Season the vinaigrette, to taste, with salt and pepper. Toss the beets in a small bowl with enough dressing to coat.'),
('8629', '4', 'Place the beets on the prepared baking sheet and roast until the beets are slightly caramelized, stirring occasionally, about 12 minutes. Set aside and cool.'),
('8629', '5', 'Toss the arugula, walnuts, and cranberries in a large bowl with enough vinaigrette to coat. Season the salad, to taste, with salt and pepper. Mound the salad atop 4 plates. Arrange the beets around the salad. Sprinkle with the avocado and goat cheese, and serve.'),
('8630', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Don''t bother to peel, but halve and seed the butternut squash, cut into 1/2-inch-thick slices, then cut each slice into four.'),
('8630', '2', 'Put the butternut pieces in a bowl with the salt, spices and 2 tablespoons oil and smoosh them about, then tip onto a lipped baking sheet (lined with aluminum foil). Don''t clean the bowl yet.'),
('8630', '3', 'Cook the squash for 30 to 40 minutes. Check to see if it is cooked through by the time the half hour''s up by piercing with a fork; some squashes cook faster than others.'),
('8630', '4', 'Add the golden raisins to the spice-smeared bowl and cover with the freshly boiled water; once cooled, whisk in the vinegar and the 2 tablespoons oil that remain.'),
('8630', '5', 'Put half of the salad leaves over a large plate or bowl and arrange the butternut pieces on top. Sprinkle with the remaining salad leaves and the toasted pine nuts. Scrape the raisin-studded dressing out of the bowl to dribble over it all and toss gently before serving.'),
('8630', '6', 'Photographs by Yunhee Kim'),
('8631', '1', 'Preheat oven to 40'),
('8631', '2', 'Toss bread cubes with butter and 2 tablespoons olive oil; add sea salt and pepper.'),
('8631', '3', 'Spread cubes in a single layer on a rimmed baking sheet.'),
('8631', '4', 'Bake at 400 for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.'),
('8631', '5', 'Mix remaining olive oil and vinegar in a large bowl to blend. Toss in arugula, chicken, toasted bread, basil, and parsley. Divide evenly onto plates, and top with Parmesan cheese.'),
('8631', '6', 'Serve warm.'),
('8632', '1', 'Make the salad: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Puree garlic and oil in a blender until smooth. Toss with potatoes, tomatoes, and thyme on a rimmed baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('8632', '2', 'Bake until potatoes are golden and tender, about 30 minutes.'),
('8632', '3', 'Let cool slightly.'),
('8633', '1', 'Mash garlic with 1/4 teaspoon salt.'),
('8633', '2', 'Whisk together garlic paste, remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, balsamic vinegar, and next 4 ingredients. Continue whisking, and slowly add oil until mixture is well blended.'),
('8633', '3', 'Toss with arugula, and garnish, if desired.'),
('8634', '1', 'Slice off top and bottom of each orange with a serrated fruit knife or sharp paring knife, removing some flesh with the peel, and reserve. With flat end of orange on a cutting board, cut off peel with a sawing motion from top to bottom, working all the way around oranges. Working over a bowl to collect juice, cut between membranes to separate orange segments, and set aside.'),
('8634', '2', 'Squeeze juice from orange tops, bottoms, and membranes into bowl (you should have about 1/2 cup), and strain into a saut pan.'),
('8634', '3', 'Add vinegar, and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to low, and simmer until reduced to about 1/4 cup, about 7 minutes.'),
('8634', '4', 'Pour hot liquid into a bowl, and whisk in olive oil in a slow, steady stream. Stir in salt and pepper.'),
('8634', '5', 'Toss arugula with fennel, onion, and 1/4 cup of dressing. Divide among 4 plates, and divide reserved orange segments among plates.'),
('8634', '6', 'Drizzle with additional dressing, and top with olives.'),
('8634', '7', 'Serve immediately.'),
('8635', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('8635', '2', 'For the dressing: In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, lemon juice, lemon zest, salt, and pepper until smooth. Set aside.'),
('8635', '3', 'For the pasta: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over high heat.'),
('8635', '4', 'Add the pasta and cook until tender but still firm to the bite, stirring occasionally, 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('8635', '5', 'Drain and reserve about 1 cup of the pasta water.'),
('8635', '6', 'In a high-sided skillet, whisk the butter over medium heat until melted. Simmer until foamy. Continue to cook until the butter has a nutty aroma and turns a caramel color, 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('8635', '7', 'Remove the pan from the heat.'),
('8635', '8', 'Add the pasta, dressing, arugula, tomatoes, Parmesan, pine nuts, and capers. Toss until coated, adding the reserved pasta water, 1 tablespoon at a time to loosen the sauce, if needed.'),
('8635', '9', 'Transfer to a large bowl and serve.'),
('8636', '1', 'Heat the oil in a large Dutch oven over a medium-high flame.'),
('8636', '2', 'Saute the carrots, onion, and celery until translucent, about 5 minutes.'),
('8636', '3', 'Add the garlic, bay leaf, thyme, and chickpeas. Cook for another 2 to 3 minutes, until the garlic is fragrant.'),
('8636', '4', 'Pour in the stock and bring to boil over high heat. Return to medium-low, and simmer, partially covered, for 15 minutes, until the veggies are very tender.'),
('8636', '5', 'Remove the thyme sprigs and bay leaf. Puree half of the mixture, either by transferring it to a blender or food processor, or by running your immersion blender through the soup until about half is smooth.Stir in the arugula off the heat. Ladle the soup into bowls and garnish with grated Parmesan cheese, a drizzle of olive oil, and crusty French bread.'),
('8638', '1', 'In a large bowl, toss the chicken, garlic, shallots, lemon zest and juice, thyme, parsley, olive oil and wine; season with salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate overnight.'),
('8638', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 42'),
('8638', '3', 'Set a rack on a rimmed baking sheet.'),
('8638', '4', 'Remove the chicken from the marinade, scraping off the solids. Arrange the chicken on the rack, skin side up. Roast for 35 to 40 minutes, until the skin is golden and crisp and an instant-read thermometer inserted in a thigh registers 16'),
('8638', '5', 'Transfer the chicken to a platter and serve with the Walnut-Arugula Pesto.'),
('8639', '1', 'Soak bamboo skewers in water 30 minutes; drain skewers.'),
('8639', '2', 'Slice each squid tube in half lengthwise. Lightly score each piece in a crisscross pattern, being careful not to cut all the way through. On each skewer, thread 1 squid piece, 2 tentacles, and another squid piece. Repeat procedure with remaining squid.'),
('8639', '3', 'Place skewers in a single layer in a 13- x 9-inch baking dish.'),
('8639', '4', 'Pour Chermoula Marinade over squid, turning to coat. Cover and chill 30 minutes.'),
('8639', '5', 'Remove squid from refrigerator, and bring to room temperature. Grill, uncovered, over high heat (400 to 45'),
('8639', '6', '45 to 60 seconds on each side or until squid is opaque. Do not overcook. Set aside.'),
('8639', '7', 'Grill bread until toasted on both sides. Rub with garlic, and drizzle with olive oil. Set aside.'),
('8639', '8', 'Drizzle 2 tablespoons Lemon Vinaigrette over arugula; toss gently.'),
('8639', '9', 'Place 1 piece of garlic toast on each serving plate; top with arugula and squid. ('),
('8639', '10', 'Remove skewers to serve, if desired.)'),
('8639', '11', 'Drizzle evenly with remaining Lemon Vinaigrette.'),
('8640', '1', 'Combine mustard and cider in a small bowl; stir well.'),
('8640', '2', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('8640', '3', 'Spread each tortilla with about 1 1/2 teaspoons mustard mixture.'),
('8640', '4', 'Place 1 tortilla, mustard side up, in pan. Arrange one-third of cheese slices over half of tortilla; cook 1 minute or until cheese begins to melt. Arrange one-third of apple slices over cheese; top with 1 cup arugula. Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Fold tortilla in half; press gently with a spatula. Cook 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown.'),
('8640', '5', 'Remove from pan. Repeat procedure twice with remaining 2 tortillas, cheese, apple slices, 2 cups arugula, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.'),
('8640', '6', 'Cut each quesadilla into 4 wedges.'),
('8640', '7', 'Wine match: Gewrztraminer. For a flavorful apple entre like these quesadillas, try a French twist with an Alsatian gewrz. The barely off-dry 2009 Helfrich "Noble Tier" Gewrztraminer (Vin D''Alsace; $1'),
('8640', '8', 'has crisp apple and melon flavors, plus some flamboyant floral (rose and gardenia) and spice components that work beautifully with the aromatic cheese and the spicy arugula. --Sara Schneider'),
('8641', '1', 'In part three of my wrap-up posts (part 1 - part'),
('8641', '2', 'you''ll get Dole''s take on "Salad 101" - and for us bloggers, that meant tasting a few salads. This vegan arugula salad that I tasted at the Dole Fresh Vegetables headquarters really won me over. So I re-made it last night - salad-licious.Here''s to the salad that saved dinnertime..Arugula Mango Avo Mac Saladinspired by Dole''s Salad Summit - makes one giant bowl1 large mango, cubed1 avocado, diced3/4 cup macadamia nuts, roasted/salted5 cups fresh arugulaoptional add-in''s: sweet onions, diced apple, diced pineapple ... moredressing (or use your own recipe):1/4 cup lemon juice2 Tbsp apple cider vinegar1/4 cup olive oil1 Tbsp Dijon mustard1 tsp agave syruppepperdash garlic powder'),
('8641', '3', 'I made a quickie salad dressing out of a few of my favorite flavors.'),
('8641', '4', 'Whisked it together and tossed it with the salad ingredients - except the arugula!'),
('8641', '5', 'I tossed the avocado, mango and nuts with the salad dressing - then poured it right over the greens. I didn''t toss the salad together until we were ready to serve the salad. Otherwise the arugula would get quite soggy.'),
('8641', '6', 'Top with fresh black pepper!'),
('8641', '7', 'Serve!..Salad to the Rescue!! Good thing I had the salad prepared, because dinner was a #fail.Last night was one of those evenings where 5pm rolls around. Then suddenly, 5pm flashes to 6pm. Then it''s 7pm and before you know it I''m still hunched over my computer at 8pm. And now suddenly I''m missing Dancing with the Stars. Gasp. Actually, maybe that''s a good thing.Type, type, type. No end in site.  "Stop working!" my brain shouts. But I trek on into the night, forgetting about dinner, forgetting about the ticking clock and feeling oh so nice about being productive."It''s 9 o''clock?" .. long pause as I stare fuzzily at my screen. Click. Off. Goodbye screen, hello dinnertime.Yes indeed, I fell back on my salad. I knew I had this giant, gorgeous salad waiting in the fridge - so really, who cares what else goes with it, right? A few smoky tempeh cubes or strips on top for added protein. We also added a few light sandwiches along side this salad feast. And it was about 11pm when we finally ate dinner. But it was a nice prize for a long day of work - diving into a giant salad bowl, my day can always end on a high note!And this salad shows a lot of restraint for me. Usually I pile on the toppings - so only 4 main ingredients - was a pleasantly delicious and simple surprise.'),
('8646', '1', 'To prepare dressing, combine first 7 ingredients in a blender; process until smooth.'),
('8646', '2', 'To prepare salad, bring 4 cups water to a boil in a large saucepan.'),
('8646', '3', 'Add shrimp; cook 1 minute.'),
('8646', '4', 'Add celery; cook 1 minute.'),
('8646', '5', 'Drain and rinse with cold water; pat dry.'),
('8646', '6', 'Place shrimp mixture, arugula, grapes, and basil in a large bowl.'),
('8646', '7', 'Drizzle with dressing; toss gently to coat. Top with cheese and walnuts.'),
('8651', '1', 'Preheat oven to 40'),
('8651', '2', 'Combine sugar, cayenne, and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a small bowl.'),
('8652', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 32'),
('8652', '2', 'On a rimmed baking sheet, arrange the tomatoes in a single layer.'),
('8652', '3', 'Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and sugar and top with the oregano.'),
('8652', '4', 'Bake for 1 hour, until the tomatoes are soft but still hold their shape. Discard the oregano.'),
('8652', '5', 'Meanwhile, in a food processor, puree 3 cups of the arugula with 1/4 cup of the olive oil until smooth. Season with salt and scrape into a bowl. Wipe out the food processor.'),
('8652', '6', 'Add the sun-dried tomatoes and 1/2 cup of the olive oil to the processor; process to a coarse puree and season with salt.'),
('8652', '7', 'In a bowl, whisk the vinegars with the vegetable oil and 1 1/2 tablespoons of the olive oil. Season with salt.'),
('8652', '8', 'Heat a nonstick skillet. Pan-fry the cheese over high heat, turning once, until well-browned and just starting to melt, 2 minutes.'),
('8652', '9', 'Transfer the scamorza to plates.'),
('8652', '10', 'In a large bowl, toss the remaining 9 cups of arugula with the dressing. Mound the salad on the plates alongside the cheese. Dot the cheese with the pestos. Arrange the tomato slices around the salad, drizzle with olive oil and serve right away.'),
('8654', '1', 'Using a sharp knife, remove the skin from the prosciutto and cut it into 1-inch pieces.'),
('8654', '2', 'Cut the prosciutto meat and fat into 1-inch pieces and coarsely grind in a meat grinder or coarsely chop in a food processor, pulsing several times.'),
('8654', '3', 'Transfer the ground prosciutto and the pieces of skin to a large soup pot.'),
('8654', '4', 'Add the carrot, onion, garlic, fennel seeds and rosemary and cook over moderate heat, stirring, until the fat is rendered, about 10 minutes.'),
('8654', '5', 'Add the cold water and bring to a boil. Simmer over moderately low heat until the broth is flavorful and reduced to 10 cups, about 1 1/2 hours. Strain the broth into a clean soup pot and refrigerate until chilled. Discard the solids.'),
('8654', '6', 'Skim the fat from the broth and discard. In a medium bowl, knead the ground pork with the egg whites and lemon juice and stir it into the cold prosciutto broth. Slowly bring the broth to a simmer, stirring constantly until the pork mixture rises completely to the top. Stir gently to dislodge any pork from the bottom of the pot. Simmer over moderately low heat, undisturbed, for 15 minutes. Using a skimmer or a slotted spoon, gently remove the "raft" from the broth and discard.'),
('8654', '7', 'Line a sieve with cheesecloth. Strain the consomm into a saucepan. Skim off any remaining fat from the surface. Season the consomm with salt and keep warm.'),
('8654', '8', 'Place the melon balls and prosciutto ribbons in 4 shallow soup bowls and top with the arugula. Ladle 1 cup of the warm consomm into each bowl and serve.'),
('8655', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400F.'),
('8655', '2', 'Spread bread cubes single layer on a rimmed baking sheet. Toast toast until very golden, about 8 to 10 minutes.Meanwhile, add asparagus to a cast iron skillet, drizzle with some olive oil. Season with salt and peppers. When croutons are done, remove and set aside to cool.'),
('8655', '3', 'Add the skillet to the oven and roast until asparagus is just tender, about 5 to 7 minutesmake sure not to overcook.'),
('8655', '4', 'Remove from oven, let cool for a minute or two, then cut into 2-inch pieces.In a deep bowl, whisk together the olive oil and balsamic vinegar.'),
('8655', '5', 'Add the honey and season with salt and pepper.'),
('8655', '6', 'Add the toasted bread cubes, asparagus, tomato, mozzarella and arugula to the bowl. Toss to coat well. Pile onto a large platter or divide among 4 to 6 small plates and serve immediately.'),
('8656', '1', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; stir with a whisk.'),
('8656', '2', 'Add arugula and pears to bowl; toss to coat.'),
('8656', '3', 'Place about 1 1/2 cups salad on each of 4 plates; sprinkle each serving with 1 tablespoon walnuts.'),
('8659', '1', 'Cook the pasta according to the package directions.'),
('8659', '2', 'Drain, rinse under cold water, and transfer to a medium bowl.'),
('8659', '3', 'Add the arugula, nuts, tomatoes, and pesto and toss.'),
('8659', '4', 'Transfer to a plate and top with the cheese.'),
('8661', '1', 'Heat oven to 350 F.'),
('8661', '2', 'Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large, ovenproof nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('8661', '3', 'Add the scallions and cook, stirring, for 1 1/2 minutes.'),
('8661', '4', 'Add the prosciutto and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly crisp, 3 to 4 minutes. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, Parmesan, and pepper.'),
('8661', '5', 'Add the cooked scallions and prosciutto.'),
('8661', '6', 'Pour the egg mixture into the skillet and stir to distribute the ingredients.'),
('8661', '7', 'Bake until browned around the edges and puffed (a knife should come out clean), 15 to 20 minutes. Meanwhile, divide the arugula among individual plates.'),
('8661', '8', 'Drizzle with the remaining olive oil, sprinkle with the salt, and top with the goat cheese.'),
('8661', '9', 'Cut the frittata into triangles and serve with the salad. Tip: If you dont own an ovenproof nonstick skillet, use a seasoned cast-iron pan instead.'),
('8662', '1', 'In a medium saucepan, combine the barley, 1 1/2 cups water, and 1/2 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until the barley is tender and the water is absorbed, about 30 minutes.'),
('8662', '2', 'Drain, spread on a rimmed baking sheet or tray, and let cool. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, whisk together the yogurt, oil, lemon juice, mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('8662', '3', 'Add the celery, apple, cooled barley, and mint (if using). Toss to combine. Divide the arugula among bowls. Top with the barley salad.'),
('8663', '1', 'Heat oven to 350 F. Slice the pork into 8 thin cutlets.'),
('8663', '2', 'Heat the oil in a large ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat. Season the pork with 1/2 teaspoon of the salt and 1/4 teaspoon of the pepper. Cook the pork until it''s browned, about 2 minutes per side. Spoon the tomato sauce over the pork. In a small bowl, combine the bread crumbs, sage, lemon zest, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon of the salt, and 1/4 teaspoon of the pepper; sprinkle evenly over the sauce. Roast until bubbling and browned, 10 minutes. Meanwhile, fill a large pot with cold water.'),
('8663', '3', 'Add the remaining salt and bring to a boil.'),
('8663', '4', 'Add the green beans and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('8663', '5', 'Drain them and plunge them into cold water to chill.'),
('8663', '6', 'Drain again and toss with the arugula.'),
('8663', '7', 'Serve with the pork.Tip: To add flavor to the green beans and arugula, toss them with butter and a squeeze of lemon. For 1/2 pound of green beans, use 2 tablespoons of melted unsalted butter and 1 tablespoon of fresh lemon juice.'),
('8664', '1', 'Gently mix arugula and nectarines in a large salad bowl.'),
('8664', '2', 'Whirl oil, lime juice, chutney, and salt in a food processor or blender until almost smooth and pour over salad. Scatter onion and hazelnuts over greens, toss, and serve immediately.'),
('8665', '1', 'Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well with a whisk.'),
('8665', '2', 'Add cantaloupe and ham; toss gently to coat.'),
('8665', '3', 'Arrange arugula in an even layer on a serving platter. Top with cantaloupe mixture; sprinkle evenly with cheese.'),
('8665', '4', 'Serve immediately.'),
('8666', '1', 'Heat oil in a large cast-iron or nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('8666', '2', 'Add onion, and saut 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in 1 teaspoon rosemary, salt, and pepper. Continue cooking 15 to 20 minutes or until onion is a deep golden brown, stirring frequently.'),
('8666', '3', 'Preheat oven to 50'),
('8666', '4', 'Roll dough into a 12-inch circle on a lightly floured surface.'),
('8666', '5', 'Place dough on a 12-inch pizza pan or baking sheet coated with cooking spray and sprinkled with cornmeal. Crimp edges of dough with fingers to form a rim. Top with onion.'),
('8666', '6', 'Bake at 500 for 10 minutes.'),
('8666', '7', 'Add cheese and walnuts; bake an additional 3 minutes or until cheese melts.'),
('8666', '8', 'Remove from oven; top with 1 teaspoon rosemary and arugula.'),
('8666', '9', 'Cut the pizza into 4 wedges.'),
('8667', '1', 'Place lemon juice and vinegar in small bowl. Gradually whisk in 1/2 cup oil. Stir in cheese. Season with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD Dressing can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.Preheat over to 375F.'),
('8667', '2', 'Heat remaining 1/3 cup olive oil in medium overproof skillet over medium heat.'),
('8667', '3', 'Add bread pieces; toss to coat.'),
('8667', '4', 'Add herbs and garlic; toss to coat.  Saut until bread is crisp, about 4 minutes.  Using slotted spoon, transfer croutons to plate in single later.  Cool.'),
('8667', '5', 'Add beets to same skillet, tossing to coat with any remaining herbs and oil. Cover skillet with foil and transfer to oven. Roast until beets are tender, about 45 minutes. Cool beets. Peel, if desired; cut in half.Toss arugula with 1/2 cup dressing in large wide bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Top with beets and croutons and serve.Thirsty for More? If you have a question about this recipe, contact our Test Kitchen at askba@bonappetit.com. To see more recipes like this one, check out our Summer Salads Slideshow.'),
('8670', '1', 'Combine 2 teaspoons garlic, 1 teaspoon pepper, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and arugula in a large bowl; toss well.'),
('8670', '2', 'Bring 4 quarts water to a boil in a large Dutch oven.'),
('8670', '3', 'Add pasta; cook 10 minutes or until al dente; drain.'),
('8670', '4', 'Add hot pasta to arugula mixture, and toss well until arugula wilts.'),
('8670', '5', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('8670', '6', 'Add shrimp, remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper; saut 1 minute.'),
('8670', '7', 'Add remaining 1 teaspoon garlic and shallots; saut 1 minute or until shrimp are done.'),
('8670', '8', 'Remove shrimp from pan.'),
('8670', '9', 'Add broth and juice to pan, scraping pan to loosen browned bits; cook 5 minutes or until liquid is reduced by half. Return shrimp to pan.'),
('8670', '10', 'Remove from heat; stir in butter.'),
('8670', '11', 'Arrange 1 1/2 cups pasta on each of 4 plates. Spoon 1/3 cup shrimp mixture over each serving. Top each serving with 2 tablespoons cheese.'),
('8673', '1', 'Preheat oven to 47'),
('8673', '2', 'Combine squash, vinegar, oil, and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a large bowl; toss well to coat. Arrange squash mixture in a single layer on a jelly-roll pan coated with cooking spray.'),
('8673', '3', 'Bake at 475 for 25 minutes or until tender and lightly browned, stirring occasionally.'),
('8673', '4', 'While squash bakes, cook pasta according to the package directions, omitting salt and fat.'),
('8673', '5', 'Drain in a colander over a bowl, reserving 1 tablespoon cooking liquid.'),
('8673', '6', 'Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('8673', '7', 'Add pine nuts, sage, and garlic; cook 3 minutes or just until the pine nuts begin to brown, stirring occasionally.'),
('8673', '8', 'Place pasta, reserved cooking liquid, pine nut mixture, and squash mixture in a large bowl; toss gently to combine.'),
('8673', '9', 'Add remaining 1/4 teaspoon of salt, arugula, cheese, and black pepper; toss gently to combine.'),
('8673', '10', 'Serve immediately.'),
('8674', '1', 'Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.'),
('8674', '2', 'Drain; keep warm.'),
('8674', '3', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('8674', '4', 'Add pepper and garlic to skillet; cook 1 minute or until garlic is fragrant.'),
('8674', '5', 'Add tomatoes; cook 45 seconds or just until heated, stirring gently.'),
('8674', '6', 'Remove the skillet from heat; stir in lemon juice and salt.'),
('8674', '7', 'Combine the hot pasta, arugula, and warm tomato mixture in a large bowl, tossing to coat. Top with cheese and bacon.'),
('8675', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('8675', '2', 'Cut bell peppers in half lengthwise; discard seeds and membranes.'),
('8675', '3', 'Place pepper halves, skin sides up, on a foil-lined baking sheet; flatten with hand. Broil 15 minutes or until blackened.'),
('8675', '4', 'Place in a zip-top plastic bag; seal.'),
('8675', '5', 'Let stand 10 minutes. Peel and cut into 1-inch strips.'),
('8675', '6', 'Cook the pasta according to the package directions, omitting salt and fat.'),
('8675', '7', 'Drain.'),
('8675', '8', 'Heat 1 teaspoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('8675', '9', 'Add 1/4 teaspoon garlic; cook 30 seconds.'),
('8675', '10', 'Add bell peppers and tomatoes to pan; cook 4 minutes or until tomatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.'),
('8675', '11', 'Remove from heat.'),
('8675', '12', 'Combine remaining 3/4 teaspoon garlic, vinegar, and next 5 ingredients (through black pepper) in a small bowl; stir with a whisk.'),
('8675', '13', 'Add pasta and oil mixture to bell pepper mixture in pan; toss well to coat. Cool slightly. Stir in arugula. Top each serving with cheese.'),
('8675', '14', 'Wine note: Fresh summer vegetables come together in Orecchiette with Roasted Peppers, Arugula, and Tomatoes, making it a good candidate for a dry ros wine. With berry and Bing cherry flavors and bright acidity, Bonterra Ros 2008 ($14), from California, is a great example of how ros complements the acid and fruitiness of tomatoes. This wine also has a slightly herbal edge, reminiscent of the dish''s herbes de Provence. --Jeffery Lindenmuth'),
('8678', '1', 'Heat a grill pan over medium-high heat. Rub thyme, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper over steaks.'),
('8678', '2', 'Add steaks to pan; cook 4 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('8678', '3', 'Remove steaks from pan.'),
('8678', '4', 'Add lemon halves, cut sides down, to pan; cook 3 minutes.'),
('8678', '5', 'Cut steaks across the grain into thin slices.'),
('8678', '6', 'Combine remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper, chives, and next 4 ingredients (through 1/8 teaspoon salt), stirring with a whisk.'),
('8678', '7', 'Drizzle over arugula; toss to coat. Arrange 1 steak, 1 cup arugula, and 1 lemon half on each of 4 plates; top each salad with 1 tablespoon cheese.'),
('8679', '1', 'To prepare salad, combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.'),
('8679', '2', 'To prepare dressing, combine vinegar and the remaining ingredients in a small bowl, stirring with a whisk until blended.'),
('8679', '3', 'Pour over salad, tossing to coat.'),
('8680', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Set a large saucepan of water to boil.'),
('8681', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients.'),
('8681', '2', 'Cut the bread loaves in half horizontally, and spread the mayonnaise mixture evenly over the cut sides of bread. Arrange 2 tomato slices over bottom half of each loaf; top with 3 tablespoons sprouts, 1 cheese slice, and 5 arugula leaves. Top with remaining bread halves, and serve immediately.'),
('8682', '1', 'Preheat oven to 40'),
('8682', '2', 'Whisk together first 2 ingredients.'),
('8682', '3', 'Place rolls on a baking sheet.'),
('8682', '4', 'Bake at 400 for 5 minutes or until lightly toasted but still soft.'),
('8682', '5', 'Let cool 10 minutes; split rolls.'),
('8682', '6', 'Spread cut sides of rolls with mayonnaise mixture. Layer bottom roll halves with beef, folding slices as needed to fit rolls. Top each with cheese, arugula, and remaining roll halves, mayonnaise mixture sides down.'),
('8683', '1', 'Butter one side only of the sliced bread according to your personal preference. On the non-buttered side of both of the slices of bread, place 1 -2 slices of cheese. ('),
('8683', '2', 'Add additional cheese if desired or if your bread slices are large)'),
